- Changed some messages in Messages.php.

- Added new buttons.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-20

- Modified the structure and the graphical interface of Configure
  Guest page in order to show a select list of sessions for each
  server.

- Modified graphical interface of Session List Guest page.

- Improved modify server procedure to avoid deleting the icon that
  is associated to the session for the guest.

- Added new application icons and new buttons.

- Defined new classes in style sheets.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-19

- Implemented FR04D01368. Added the possibility to access the NX
  Builder as a Guest Builder User. The administrator defines and
  configures which sessions will be deployed for the Guest Builder
  User.

- Modified the graphical interface of ConfigureGuest, SessionList
  Guest, AddServer and ModifyServer pages.

- According to new modifications, the structure of the servers and
  sessions tables and the insert and update server procedures have 
  been modified.

- Modified create session file procedure to specify if the connection
  to the server will be encrypted or unencrypted.

- Modified javascript function to show the image uploaded in the Se-
  lect Icon field.

- Added javascript function to disable the choosing of the resolution
  when a custom session is launched.

- Added favicon.ico showing NX logo in the address bar of browser.

- Added javascript functions to enable or disable some fields in
  add and modify server pages.

- Added new toolbar images.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-18

- Added create and modify guest user procedures. The administrator of
  NX Builder defines a list of sessions that a user, logged as a 
  guest, can run.

- Improved display of applications list. Now only the application is 
  shown and not all the path. 
  
- Added javascript functions to handle the passage of options between
  some selects.
  
- Added procedure to create session files to allow connections on
  NX Server as a guest user.
  
- Added javascript function to disable username and password fields
  when the user is logging as a guest.

- Implemented ServerListGuest to show the list of sessions available
  for a guest user.  
  
- Added new class in style sheets.

- Improved configure guest procedure: the administrator can define
  the login mode on the NX server for the NX Builder Guest User.
  
- Modified the graphical interface of ServerListGuest and Configure
  Guest pages.
  
- Modified setup procedure, now the dates inserted are stored in the
  fields also when the form is submitted.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-17

- Modified connect procedure. Now nxbuilder generates a dynamic page
  passing the proper content type inside the page, without saving the
  file in a directory of the web server. 

- Changed some messages in Messages.php.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-16

- Modified the server list page for the administrator. Now the Add 
  server button is shown when the server list is empty.

- Modified create and modify users procedures. Added new checkbox for
  the credentials to access NX Server. When it is unselected, NX
  Builder will create the session file without specifying username 
  and password. 

- Modified the user list. Now an icon shows if the user uses the same
  credentials of NX Builder to access the NX Server. 
  
- Modified the graphical interface for displaying messages.

- Added check on add and modify server procedures, now a message is
  shown when the administrator has not selected a desktop. 
  
nxbuilder-2.0.0-15

- Modified the graphical interface of all procedures.

- Modified create and modify server procedures. Now an error message
  is shown if the server port is not a numeric value.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-14

- Modified create sessions file procedure. The custom session is
  configured to be a 'Floating Window'.

- Added javascript function to check the operating system so that the
  end-user is redirected to the proper download page to download the 
  NX Client package for his/her O.S.

- Modified modify, create server and user procedures, now the dates
  inserted are stored in the fields also when the form is submitted.

- Moved the nxbuilder/readme-info file to nxbuilder/documents/builder
  /readme-info.

- Add the nxbuilder/documents/builder/license-info file.

- Added javascript function in procedure to add and to modify users.
  Now the server list is shown only when the user doesn't have the
  administrator privileges.

- Fixed the update procedure to save properly to the DB changes on ù
  the server.

- Added new icon for info button.

- Modified the graphical interface to show the server list and the
  information about the servers.
    
nxbuilder-2.0.0-13

- Added a procedure to create session files to allow connections to
  application running in a rootless X11 session.

- Added check to verify if the directory, where the session files are 
  to be stored,exists. If not, the directory is created.
  
- Modified modify user procedure to fit the new structure of the 
  database.

- Added info button to display the server information. The NX Builder 
  administrator can choose if enabling or not the displaying of the
  server information.
  
- Changed procedures to modify server according to the new structure
  of the database.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-12

- Modified the way the VNC password is stored in the database to use
  the same format adopted by NXClient.
  
- Modified procedure to create session files. Now it is possible to 
  to specify the name of the directory where they will be saved.

- Modified the database structure to allow restrictions on the user's
  sessions.
  
- Modified insert and select user procedures to fit the new structure 
  of the database.
  
- Modified insert and select servers procedures.
  
nxbuilder-2.0.0-11

- Added procedure to create session files to allow connections to RDP 
  and VNC servers. 

- Modified javascript functions to add and remove commands in create
  and modify server pages.
  
- Changed the name of the session files and the directory where they
  are stored.

- Removed RDP domain field from the settings for the Windows session.

- Replaced 'Create User' button with 'Add User' button.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-10

- Modified procedures to create and modify server. Now it is possible 
  to add and configure the following desktop types: xdm, rdp, custom 
  and windows.   

- Added javascript functions to hide or display input fields related 
  to rdp, windows and custom deskto types.

- Added new fields to the server DB table.

- Updated CHANGELOG to correctly include missing references to FRs.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-9

- Implemented FR10C01089 to deploy X11 sessions via NX Builder, as
  desktop Unix-KDE, Unix-GNOME and Unix-CDE.
  
- Improved code in order to run NX Builder on Internet Explorer for 
  Windows. 

- Added new style for supporting Internet Explorer browser.

- Added function.js file. It contains javascript functions to add and 
  delete servers and users.
  
- Added checks in order to ensure the access to web pages only if the
  user is logged. 

nxbuilder-2.0.0-8

- Modified setup procedure. Now it is possible choosing if updating 
  the application or creating a new database.

- Modified upload procedure to check if the uploaded file is an image
  or not.
 
- Renamed files: conf.php to builder.cfg, Colour.php to Color.php, 
  nxbuilder.conf to builder.conf to be standard compliant.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-7

- Added nxbuilder.conf file, it contains configuration paramaeters 
  to run the NX Builder application.
  
- Modified conf.php file to allow to personalize the connection to 
  database.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-6
  
- Modified the connection procedure. Now it's possible to execute 
  the session file without downloading it.

- Added new style in win_mz.css and lin_mz.css files.

