nxbuilder-2.0.0-5
  
- Updated the source code to be compliant to the NX standards.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-4

- Changed message shown by the NX Builder application.

- Modified the graphic to add or to modify the list of servers for
  the user.

nxbuilder-2.0.0-3

- Updated the NoMachine copyright notices. 

- Added new graphical template and new buttons.

- Added setup.php and configuration.php files to create the database
  backend for NX Builder and to generate the conf.php file containing
  all the parameters needed for connecting to the database.

- Implemented new functionS to delete and to modify either users and 
  servers.

- When the administrator creates a new server, it is possible to
  associate an image to this server. The image can be uploaded and
  stored on the Web server side.
   
- Added messages.php file that contains all the messages displayed by
  NX Builder. 

- Added userList.php file to display the list of the NX Builder users 
  created by the administrator.

- Added the readme-info file to NX builder.
  
- Changed names of some variables. 

nxbuilder-2.0.0-2

- Implemented administration interface to create basic session files 
  to start sessions on the NX servers listed in the Web Application.
  The interface allows the administrator to add NX servers to the web
  application and to create new accounts for users of the NX Builder.

- Implemented login to the Web Application as user: once the user
  is logged to the Web Application, he/she will be redirected on
  the page showing the list of the available NX servers for the user.
  For each NX server displayed, there will be the possibility to
  choose some basics options to configure the NX session and click
  on the link 'Start NX session' to run the session on the NX server.

- Added link Start NX session that will check if the NX client is
  installed on the user's machine. If the NX client is not installed
  on the user's machine, the Web Application will inform the user 
  that he needs to: install the NX Client or to use NX Web Companion.

- When the users clicks on the link to start the session, the NX
  Builder will create the session file and return the .nxs mime type.

- Modified scramblig algorithm for saving the password in the session
  file in a scrambled format so that is possible to automate login.
  
nxbuilder-2.0.0-1

- Opened the 2.0.0 branch based on the 1.5.0-1. 

nxbuilder-1.5.0-1

- Initial development of the NX Client Profile Builder Sample.
